openapi: 3.0.1 info: title: FatFree REST Api description: FATIGUE ANALYSIS OF FREE SPANNING PIPELINES version: v1 servers: - url: https://api.veracity.com/ext/dnvgl/fatfree/v1 paths: /api/Fatigue/F105: post: tags: - F105 summary: Calculates damage and fatigue life for standard single location span definitions. description: "This endpoint accepts all input combinations available in the FatFree 13 desktop application when the\r\nResopnse data option is set to any other value than 'User defined'.\r\n\r\nSchema: F105Input\r\n\r\nKey input options:\r\n \r\nMetocean:\r\n
  • Current input: Weibull, Rpv and Histogram
  • Wave input: Weibull, Rpv, Histogram, Scatter tables and NoWave
    • \r\n\r\nBoundary conditions: F105 Span, Pinned-Pinned, Pinned-Fixed, Fixed-Fixed\r\n\r\nSoil (damping and stiffness): 10 pre-defined soils as well as direct specification of values\r\n\r\nSN curves (root and cap): 18 pre-defined curves as well as direct specification\r\n \r\n\r\nAll of the above examples are given as separate json objects inside the main F105Input schema. Consult the\r\nexamples and schema descriptions for details." operationId: post-api-fatigue-f105 requestBody: content: application/json-patch+json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/F105Input' application/json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/F105Input' text/json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/F105Input' application/*+json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/F105Input' responses: '200': description: Success content: application/json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/FatigueLifeResults' '400': description: Invalid or insufficient input. This includes valid input that is outside the model ranges. '500': description: Calculation error. Unhandled exceptions. /api/Fatigue/MultiLocationModeShape: post: tags: - MultiLocationModeShape summary: Calculates damage and fatigue life for multi-location F105 span definitions given modes shape as input. description: "This endpoint accepts all input combinations available in the FatFree 13 desktop application when the\r\nResponse data option is set to 'User defined' and the MultiMode calculation option is set to\r\n'Mode shape input only'.\r\n\r\nSchema: MultiLocationModeShapeInput\r\n\r\nKey input options:\r\n \r\nMetocean:\r\n
  • Current input: Weibull, Rpv and Histogram
  • Wave input: Weibull, Rpv, Histogram, Scatter tables and NoWave
    • \r\n\r\nSoil (damping): 10 pre-defined soils as well as direct specification of values. Note that soil stiffness\r\nis not used for the multi-location calculations.\r\n \r\nLocation array (x-axis of each modeshape array)\r\n \r\nModeshape arrays (two-dimensional, one modeshape per row)\r\n \r\nFrequency array (single-dimensional), each element matching the associated modeshape\r\n\r\nSN curves (root and cap): 18 pre-defined curves as well as direct specification\r\n \r\n\r\nAll of the above examples are given as separate json objects or json arrays inside the main\r\nMultiLocationModeShapeInput schema. Consult the examples and schema descriptions for details." operationId: post-api-fatigue-multilocationmodeshape requestBody: content: application/json-patch+json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/ModeShapeInput' application/json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/ModeShapeInput' text/json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/ModeShapeInput' application/*+json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/ModeShapeInput' responses: '200': description: Success '400': description: Invalid or insufficient input. This includes valid input that is outside the model ranges. '500': description: Calculation error. Unhandled exceptions. /api/Fatigue/MultiLocationStressAmplitude: post: tags: - MultiLocationStressAmplitude summary: Calculates damage and fatigue life for multi-location F105 span definitions given unit diameter stress amplitudes as input. description: "This endpoint accepts all input combinations available in the FatFree 13 desktop application when the\r\nResponse data option is set to 'User defined' and the MultiMode calculation option is set to\r\n'Direct stress amplitude input'.\r\n\r\nSchema: MultiLocationStressAmplitudeInput\r\n\r\nKey input options:\r\n \r\nMetocean:\r\n
  • Current input: Weibull, Rpv and Histogram
  • Wave input: Weibull, Rpv, Histogram, Scatter tables and NoWave
    • \r\n\r\nSoil (damping): 10 pre-defined soils as well as direct specification of values. Note that soil stiffness\r\nis not used for the multi-location calculations.\r\n \r\nLocation array (x-axis of the stress amplitude arrays for each mode)\r\n \r\nUnit diameter stress amplitude array (two-dimensional, one row per mode)\r\n \r\nFrequency array (single-dimensional), each element matching the associated stress amplitude array\r\n\r\nSN curves (root and cap): 18 pre-defined curves as well as direct specification\r\n \r\n\r\nAll of the above examples are given as separate json objects or json arrays inside the main\r\nMultiLocationStressAmplitudeInput schema. Consult the examples and schema descriptions for details." operationId: post-api-fatigue-multilocationstressamplitude requestBody: content: application/json-patch+json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/StressAmplitudeInput' application/json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/StressAmplitudeInput' text/json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/StressAmplitudeInput' application/*+json: schema: $ref: '#/components/schemas/StressAmplitudeInput' responses: '200': description: Success '400': description: Invalid or insufficient input. This includes valid input that is outside the model ranges. '500': description: Calculation error.
